-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Project description

Space for extensions and additional plugins for dijit.Editor 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Dependencies:

dijit.Editor
dijit.Menu
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Documentation

Editor.js, html.js, range.js, RichText.js, selection.js are all part of
an experimental rewrite of the dijit.Editor which is known to have serious
regressions.  See #6582, #5707.  This code may be merged back to dijit or abandoned.

plugins
Unrelated to the editor rewrite.  Plugins which work with dijit.Editor.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Plugin Installation instructions

Get the dojox/editor folder (and dojox/editor/plugins) from the 
dojox SVN repository. Include the Editor and plugins in your page:

dojo.require("dijit.Editor");
dojo.require("dojox.editor.plugins.TablePlugins");
dojo.require("dojox.editor.plugins.UploadImage");

And the style sheet:

<link href="[path]dojox/editor/plugins/resources/editorPlugins.css" type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" />
<link href="[path]dojox/form/resources/FileInput.css" type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" />

See tests for examples:
dojox/editor/plugins/tests/editorTablePlugs.html
dojox/editor/plugins/tests/editorUploadPlug.html
